<tt>Mon Feb 10  3:19:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
You say that we lost the war because &quot;we did not have the resolve.&quot; You imply that we could have somehow won the war. How is that? What was the secret way of winning the war. Several administrations and hundreds of people in the government would have done everything in their power to get ahold of this golden secret you pretend to possess. How could we have won the war? We killed two million North Vietnamese but that didn't enable us to win the war. Where do you bomb in a pre-industrial country? Do you bomb rice patties? The Americans fought the war through &quot;attrition&quot; which is overwhelming force. This is similar to what the British used during the American Revolution. The North Vietnamese fought through &quot;manuver&quot; which laying low, hit and run tactics, fabian tactics, guerrilla warfare, etc. This is similar to what the American colonists used during the American Revolution. In a war, your goal is to eliminate the ability of your enemy to wage war. There is no way we could have eliminated the North Vietnamese's ability to wage war. If we had blasted all of North Vietnam into oblivion. they would have hunkered down in caves and tunnels, and then continued to kill Americans, as long as Americans remained in their country. Perhaps we could have defeated them if we used nuclear weopons, but the Soviets might respond. You would be risking global thermonuclear war. Do you think that throughout the war, the American leaders were not doing everything in their power to win the war? They were desparate to win the war. They did everything they could think of. We realized that we weren't capable of defeating the North Vietnamese militarily. The North Vietnamese would have fought to the last man. The Tet Offensive underscored how utterly futile this war was. You say that we didn't win because &quot;we did not have the resolve.&quot; What pray tell was your secret formula foe winning the war? The American leaders did everything they could have done. They should have recognized the handwriting on the wall much earlier.
